La Casita first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]],<ref name=2010CensusTX/> one of nine CDPs ([[Amada Acres, Texas|Amada Acres]], [[Chaparrito, Texas|Chaparrito]], La Casita, [[Loma Linda East, Starr County, Texas|Loma Linda East]], [[Manuel Garcia, Texas|Manuel Garcia]], [[Manuel Garcia II, Texas|Manuel Garcia II]], [[Olivia Lopez de Gutierrez, Texas|Olivia Lopez de Gutierrez]], [[Ramirez-Perez, Texas|Ramirez-Perez]], [[Victoria Vera, Texas|Victoria Vera]]) carved out of the deleted [[La Casita-Garciasville, Texas|La Casita-Garciasville CDP]].<ref name=2010CensusTX/>

